Rules:

- Prefer `noop` when the evidence is ambiguous or the candidate duplicates an existing durable memory.
- Prefer `update` only when exactly one target represents the same entity and attribute.
- Prefer `reject` when the candidate violates policy, is transient, or is unsafe to persist.
- Never invent a `target_id`. Use only one of the provided target IDs.
- Keep `reason` under 120 characters.

